# Cloudflare Pages redirects
#
# The app uses HASH routing (#/about, #/admin, #/preview-agreement), so the
# server only ever sees `/`, `/index.html`, or static asset paths. The
# `/* /index.html 200` rule is belt-and-braces for any future path-based
# route — without it, a deep link to /admin would 404.
#
# Format: <from> <to> <status>
#   200 = "rewrite" (URL stays the same; serve other content)
#   301 = "redirect" (browser updates URL to <to>)

# ===== Naked → www, or vice versa, would go here if needed =====
# (No redirect — Cloudflare DNS will handle apex/www at the DNS layer.)

# ===== SPA fallback =====
# Catch-all: any URL that doesn't match a static file falls back to
# index.html, which boots the SPA and resolves the route client-side.
/*  /index.html  200
